{"title_page": "Kuttichathan", "text_new": "{{other uses|Kuttichathan (disambiguation)}}\n{{pp-30-500|small=yes}}\n\n'''Kuttichathan''' is a mischievous [[demon]] in [[Malabar region|Malabar]] demonology. He is a well-nourished 12 year old who is sometimes described having a [[forelock]].<ref name=\":0\" /> Some of Kuttichathan's tricks are agonizing (his victims' clothes might turn on fire, their food might turn into [[excrement]], their beds might become a bed of [[Thorns, spines, and prickles|thorns]]), but they never do any serious harm.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.70013|title=Lectures On Ethnography|last=Iyer|first=L. K. Ananthakrishna|date=1925|publisher=|isbn=|location=|pages=[https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.70013/page/n259 197]\u2013198|author-link=L. K. Ananthakrishna Iyer}} {{PD-notice}}</ref> Kuttichathan only requests food in return for his services.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nIn [[Kerala]], Kuttichathan is believed to be vengeful with people who stop trying to appease him. If they do not sacrifice a cock on a regular basis with the correct incantations, Kuttichathan will instill fear by playing horrendous pranks on a family causing them misery.<ref name=\"Kapur1983\">{{cite book|author=Sohaila Kapur|title=Witchcraft in western India|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=VdM6AAAAMAAJ|year=1983|publisher=Orient Longman|page=4}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n\n* [https://archive.org/details/dli.MoI.Therayattam_Eng Therayattam \u2013 Worship Dances of Malabar.] A 1958 documentary showing worship dances of Malabar, with a dance dedicated to Kuttichathan shown at 09:30. [[Ministry_of_Information_(India)|Indian Ministry of Information]], [[OCLC]] [https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/4702509 4702509]. \n\n[[Category:Demons]]\n\n\n{{India-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{other uses|Kuttichathan (disambiguation)}}\n{{pp-30-500|small=yes}}\n\n'''Kuttichathan''' is a mischievous [[demon]] in [[Malabar region|Malabar]] demonology. He is a well-nourished 12 year old who is sometimes described having a [[forelock]].<ref name=\":0\" /> Some of Kuttichathan's tricks are agonizing (his victims' clothes might turn on fire, their food might turn into [[excrement]], their beds might become a bed of [[Thorns, spines, and prickles|thorns]]), but they never do any serious harm.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.70013|title=Lectures On Ethnography|last=Iyer|first=L. K. Ananthakrishna|date=1925|publisher=|isbn=|location=|pages=[https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.70013/page/n259 197]\u2013198|author-link=L. K. Ananthakrishna Iyer}} {{PD-notice}}</ref> Kuttichathan only requests food in return for his services.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nIn [[Kerala]], Kuttichathan is believed to be vengeful with people who stop trying to appease him. If they do not sacrifice a cock on a regular basis with the correct incantations, Kuttichathan will instill fear by playing horrendous pranks on a family causing them misery.<ref name=\"Kapur1983\">{{cite book|author=Sohaila Kapur|title=Witchcraft in western India|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=VdM6AAAAMAAJ|year=1983|publisher=Orient Longman|page=4}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n\n* [https://archive.org/details/dli.MoI.Therayattam_Eng Therayattam \u2013 Worship Dances of Malabar.] A 1958 documentary showing worship dances of Malabar, with a dance dedicated to Kuttichathan shown at 09:30. [[Ministry_of_Information_(India)|Indian Ministry of Information]], [[OCLC]] [https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/4702509 4702509]. \n\n[[Category:Demons]]\n\n{{india-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Paine Ellsworth", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:fmt", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kuttichathan"}
